<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-457] test/cpp makefiles do not honor --prefix configuration setting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-457</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The test/cpp/Stress-test.mk and test/cpp/Thrift-test.mk makefiles do not use the include or library paths defined by the --prefix configuration parameter. This makes the test program builds fail because header files and libraries (once you fix the header paths) cannot be found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I cannot provide a patch because I don&apos;t know how to make this change, other than by editing the makefiles in my source tree. I&apos;m sure there&apos;s some automake way to fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;All&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
